BitField.Name: AIDACA1_SEL
BitField.Documentation: Input data selection (from input audio data interface) 00: Left data 01: Right data 10: Average between left and right data 11: Null data (hard mute).

BitField.Name: AI_UNLOCK
BitField.Documentation: AI unlock status event flag, refer to section ref{RegType-IFR} Flag is raised when audio interface sample frequency in slave mode is not consistent with programmed value.

BitField.Name: AI_UNLOCK_MASK
BitField.Documentation: AI unlock flag mask, refer to section ref{RegType-IMR}.

BitField.Name: BIASA_POWER_MODE

BitField.Name: DACA12_DRC_EN
BitField.Documentation: Activation of soft clipping DRC on DACA12 0: Inactive 1: Active.

BitField.Name: DACA1_COMP
BitField.Documentation: Soft clipping DRC compression for DAC A1 channel 000: 1 001: 2 step x2 100: 16 101: 32 Higher than 101: Reserved for Dolphin's usage.

BitField.Name: DACA1_SOFT_MUTE
BitField.Documentation: DAC A1 soft mute mode 0: Soft mute inactive 1: Soft mute active.

BitField.Name: DACA1_THRES
BitField.Documentation: Soft clipping DRC compression threshold for DAC A1 channel 00000: Full scale 00001: Full scale -1 dB 00010: Full scale -2 dB by step of -1 dB 11110: Full scale -30 dB 11111: Full scale -31 dB.

BitField.Name: DACA_ADWL
BitField.Documentation: DACA Audio Data Word Length selection 00: 16-bit word length data 01: 18-bit word length data 10: 20-bit word length data 11: 24-bit word length data.

BitField.Name: DACA_AUDIOIF
BitField.Documentation: Input audio data interface protocol selection for stream A 00: Parallel 11: I2S Others: Reserved for Dolphin's usage.

BitField.Name: DACA_FLT_CFG_SEL
BitField.Documentation: DACA Filter chain auto configuration selection 000 : High Filtering mode 001: Balanced Filtering mode 010: Low latency Filtering mode Others: Reserved for further use.

BitField.Name: DACA_FREQ
BitField.Documentation: Input audio data interface sampling rate selection (Fs) for stream A 0000: 8 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 0010: 11.025 kHz with 22.5792 MHz main clock frequency 0010: 12 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 0011: 16 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 0101: 22.05 kHz with 22.5792 MHz main clock frequency 0101: 24 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 0110: 32 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 1000: 44.1 KHz with 22.5792 MHz main clock frequency 1000: 48 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 1010: 96 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 1100: 192 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 1101: 384 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency 1110: 768 kHz with 24.576 MHz main clock frequency Others: Reserved for further use.

BitField.Name: DACA_SLAVE
BitField.Documentation: Input audio data interface master/slaveness selection for stream A 0: ViC audio interface is master 1: ViC audio interface is slave.

BitField.Name: DAC_BYPASS
BitField.Documentation: DAC bypass feature selection 00: No bypass. Digital filters part and analog part are working together. 01: Digital filters bypass. Digital filters part is not working. Analog part input data come from top ports. 10: Analog part bypass. Analog part is not working. Data from digital filters are available on top ports. Others: Reserved for Dolphin's usage.

BitField.Name: DAC_SAT
BitField.Documentation: DAC saturation detection event flag, refer to section ref{RegType-IFR} Flag is raised when a saturation in the DAC has been detected.

BitField.Name: DAC_SAT_MASK
BitField.Documentation: DAC saturation detection flag mask, refer to section ref{RegType-IMR}.

BitField.Name: DAC_SMUTE_IN_PROGRESS
BitField.Documentation: DACA soft mute status 0: DACA digital filters are operating in accordance with DACA*_SOFT_MUTE value 1: DACA digital filters are being updated after a recent change in DACA*_SOFT_MUTE value.

BitField.Name: GOD_DACA1
BitField.Documentation: DAC A1 digital gain programming value 1000000: -64 dB 1000001: -63 dB by step of 1 dB 1111111: -1 dB 0000000: 0 dB 0000001: 1 dB by step of 1 dB 0111111: 63 dB.

BitField.Name: INT_FORM
BitField.Documentation: Waveform and polarity of the IRQ signal 00: The generated IRQ is a high level 01: The generated IRQ is a low level 10: The generated IRQ is a high level pulse with at least a 8 MCLK cycles duration 11: The generated IRQ is a low level pulse with at least a 8 MCLK cycles duration.

BitField.Name: IRQ_PENDING
BitField.Documentation: Pending IRQ status 0: ViC does not have any pending interrupt request on IRQ output 1: ViC has generated at least one interrupt request on IRQ output that has not been handled yet.

BitField.Name: MCLK_FREQ_SEL
BitField.Documentation: Indication of MCLK frequency 001: 24.576 MHz 100: 22.5792 MHz.

BitField.Name: NEN_PULLD

BitField.Name: NEN_SAT_DET
